cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.RO 

Reasoning: The paper focuses on self-supervised learning of feature embeddings for matching correspondences along videos, which is a task related to computer vision and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel information bottleneck and a recursive model, which are related to deep learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely categories as well. Additionally, the paper achieves state-of-the-art performance on video segmentation and keypoint tracking tasks, which are related to multimedia (cs.MM) and robotics (cs.RO) applications.
